Predicate Expression Syntax for Datasets
The predicate expression must have the following syntax: <dataset column> <operator> <value>
For example, you can define the predicate expression for a dataset: 'UserId' == "$User.Id"
You include at least one dataset column as part of the predicate expression.
The value in the predicate expression can be a string literal or number literal.
You can use the backslash character (\) to escape characters in column names and string values in a predicate expression.
CRM Analytics supports UTF-8 characters in dataset column names and values in a predicate expression.
